[normal]3.3 [bold]Does UK industry benefit more widely from the UK’s position as a centre for extractive industries i.e. In sales of machinery and services to international businesses in the sector?[bold]&#xa0;[bold]Glencore actively seeks to purchase products and services locally as far as possible, according to specific need. Typically we purchase maintenance services, catering supplies, transportation and basic construction materials locally, amongst a range of oth
[normal]er items depending on local availability. Local purchasing provides quick access and also reduces the costs and environmental impact associated with transporting materials. In addition, our support of the local economy helps to fund local services includin
[normal]g those that meet health and education needs.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]In 2012, Britannia Refined Metals, our lead refinery in north Kent, spent £9 million on procurement, 
[normal]of which 
[normal]less than 4% was with non-UK suppliers. Of its total 218 suppliers, only 8 were non-UK companies.
