[normal]3.5[bold] [bold]What[bold] are the corporate governance concerns raised by the number of extractive industries companies listed in the UK? Are there reputational risks for the UK and UK financial institutions in being a centre for such businesses?[bold]&#xa0;[bold]Glencore believes that high corpo
[normal]rate governance standards are a pre-requisite for properly functioning financial markets. Meeting the listing and corporate governance requirements of the London market may be a challenge for some companies but such hurdles provide comfort and protection f
[normal]or investors and, ultimately, benefit
[normal] the reputation of the City of London and the UK, generally.
[normal]  
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Extractive companies are not, in themselves, a reputational risk. G
[normal]lencore 
[normal]and other companies of similar stature in the mining and energy sectors are 
[normal]required to comply with extensive regulation in numerous jurisdictions relating to health, safe
[normal]ty, the environment, the control
[normal] of industrial processes as well 
[normal]as 
[normal]tax and corporate governance matters. G
[normal]lencore
[normal] is scrupulous in its adherence to all relevant
[normal] legislation. Reput
[normal]ational risk typically arises where businesses 
[normal]suffer from weak management, 
[normal]the failure of
[normal] individual
[normal]s and where there is poor internal and external oversight of corporate governance standards.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The corporate governance concerns which have been raised do not apply to the main FTSE 100 resources companies such Shell, BP, Glencore, BHP Billiton, Rio and Anglo American. Rather these concerns have been raised in respect of the 
[normal]small number of companie
[normal]s
[normal] with a dominant or very significant shareholder or shareholders based 
[normal]i
[normal]n jurisdiction
[normal]s
[normal] 
[normal]which 
[normal]lack 
[normal]a strong track record in corporate governance. Such companies are not exclusively 
[normal]limited 
[normal]to the extract
[normal]ive
[normal] industries sector but the recent focus on these 
[normal]reflect
[normal]s
[normal] 
[normal]the 
[normal]significant 
[normal]number of 
[normal]listings 
[normal]by extractive companies 
[normal]in the 2000s.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The UK Stewardship Code provides an additional mechanism by which investors can improve the governance of listed companies by monitoring the performance of directors and the
[normal] fulfilment of their duties to investors and other stakeholders. 
